<SLUG> BC-BICKLEY-COLUMN-AZR </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
SOME SCATTERED SHOTS, OBSERVATIONS, SUGGESTIONS 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
 By DAN BICKLEY  
 c.1999 The Arizona Republic  
<TEXT>
<P>
   Suddenly, Cheryl Miller and I have two things in common: We both
got a haircut and neither one of us is coaching the Mercury.
</P>
<P>
   MSNBC is predicting the Suns will use the ninth pick to draft
Northwestern's Evan Eschmeyer, who is 6 feet 11, 245 pounds, very
slow and very much in need of a tan. Or, as the Web site explains,
just ``the kind of player that Jerry Colangelo covets.''
</P>
<P>
   Just when you thought it was safe to embrace the Cardinals:
After getting squashed by the Rio Salado vote, the Bidwill clan was
bathing in sympathy. They became legitimate martyrs. People were
vowing to never spend another cent in Mesa. Support was filtering
in from all sides.
</P>
<P>
   Now you learn that the $75 million the Cardinals were willing to
contribute wasn't exactly their money. That some of it _ and I'm
guessing all but $16 _ was floated by the NFL as an interest-free
loan.
</P>
<P>
   This is how you earn voter distrust. The kind that lingers for
11 years.
</P>
<P>
   Tennis historian Bud Collins insists that until Pete Sampras
wins the French Open, he can never be considered the best player in
history. Like playing tennis in a sandbox counts for anything.
</P>
<P>
   Two area athletes requiring an interpreter for our benefit:
Byung-Hyun Kim and Simeon Rice.
</P>
<P>
   The decline of local sports radio was unavoidable, a domino
effect triggered by the devastating loss of the three-tooth wonder,
the Howard Stern of the Harley crowd, that painful reminder that
nothing is as blind as a microphone . . .
</P>
<P>
   Anyone else miss Wild Bill?
</P>
<P>
   Say it isn't so: The Suns need to get tough, they need a
presence on the blocks, they have a $2 million exception and, just
the other night, Charles Barkley was wandering through Bank One
Ballpark.
</P>
<P>
   If he returns to the Valley to train, fine. It's a free country.
But in the name of civic sophistication, do not refer to a
convicted rapist and prison veteran as ``Phoenix's own Mike
Tyson.''
</P>
<P>
   And unless you want to sound like a hick town lost in the
cornfields, how about a moratorium on Tom Gugliotta's nickname?
</P>
<P>
   During last year's stretch run, Jamir Miller requested a chat
with Vince Tobin. He told the coach he wanted to rush the passer.
Tobin thanked Miller for coming by, but if he didn't mind, the
Cardinals happened to be in playoff race and there was no time for
such individual, egotistical, salary-drive nonsense.
</P>
<P>
   All together now: Vince! Vince! Vince! Vince!
</P>
<P>
   Now that he's down to about two at-bats per week, Bernard Gilkey
might want to check whether his credit cards still work in Arizona.
</P>
<P>
   Why you can't beat Mike Keenan: Once in Montreal, Keenan walked
into a bar. He started singing along with a classic tune from the
Everly Brothers. He spotted a Canadian columnist he knew and
demanded that the scribe sing along with him. When that columnist
ignored the directive, Keenan simply punched the fellow in the
chest, sending a mug of beer skyward.
</P>
<P>
   Soon, the columnist was singing like a parakeet.
</P>
<P>
   Shandon Anderson is a free agent and would look great in a Suns
uniform.
</P>
<P>
   New Arizona: Jake Plummer, Jason Kidd, Travis Lee, Rob Evans.
</P>
<P>
   Old Arizona: Open roads, Al McCoy, Bruce Snyder, Cotton
Fitzsimmons.
</P>
<P>
   And three traditions ready for retirement: The Sun City Dancers,
The Gorilla, The Whiteout.
</P>
<P>
   It's safe to assume that Daniel Snyder, a 34-year-old who paid
$800 million for the Washington Redskins, never held a paper route.
</P>
<P>
   Of all the ex-Blackhawks goalies looming in the NHL, it figures
that Dominik Hasek is in Buffalo, Eddie Belfour is in Dallas and
you end up with Jimmy Waite.
</P>
<P>
   Now that the Arizona Wildcats are set to open the season as
national championship contenders, can someone please explain what
happened to Sun Devils football?
</P>
<P>
   Another reason for the ouster of Jim Schoenfeld: A new coach
will sound a lot more appetizing to Robert Reichel, a skilled softy
pondering a permanent return to Europe.
</P>
<P>
   And a little advice for Gregg Olson, who is refusing to speak to
the media over earlier ``negativity,'' as he called it: Take a look
around. Pick up the tabloids. And be thankful you're not making a
living in New York. &QL; 
Dan Bickley can be reached at dan.bickley(at)pni.com via e-mail. &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
