<P>
   CAR-STEWART _ INDIANAPOLIS and CONCONRD, N.C. _ It was a
logistical nightmare for NASCAR driver Tony Stewart, who raced in
the Indy 500 during the morning, then rushed by helicopter and
company plane to Charlotte for the Coke 600 that night. After
spending the day with Stewart, a forner open-wheel driver and
rookie on the NASCAR circuit, we chronicle the timeline.
(Schlabach, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 60.
