<P>
   CAR-TRAGEDY _ Vickie Pyatte was watching a television show
several weeks ago when the station interrupted the telecast with a
scroll across the bottom of the screen. ``Spectators injured,
possibly killed during accident at Lowe's Motor Speedway.'' Just to
satisfy her concern, Vicki dialed the cell phone of her son, who
was attending his first race. She knew something was wrong when
there was no answer. What followed has been a nightmare for the
Pyatte family, which is trying to cope with the death of Randy,
their 21-year-old son, who was one of three killed by flying debris
after a crash of open-wheel race cars at at Lowe's. ``When you go
to the racetrack to watch a race, you're not supposed to die,''
Vickie said. (Schlabach, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). WITH
PHOTOS. MOVED.BASEBALL
