<SLUG> BC-RAC-TRIPLE-CROWN-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
LUKAS COULD BE EDGE AS CHARISMATIC GOES FOR SWEEP
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By RANDY MOSS 
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
 
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   The last time a horse swept the Triple Crown races, little
Stevie Cauthen wasn't shaving yet. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Chris Antley was 12 years old and thought jockeys were something
you wore under your pants. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Bill Clinton was the youngest attorney general in Arkansas
history. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Ronald Reagan was still trying to get elected president _ and
few gave him a chance. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   The last 3-year-old .MDBO/[ .MDNM/race.MDBO/].MDNM/horse to pull
off the feat was Affirmed in 1978. But on Saturday, an underdog
colt named Charismatic will attempt to capture the Belmont Stakes
and become racing's 12th Triple Crown winner. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   History says the odds are against him. Twenty-seven horses have
won both the Kentucky Derby and Preakness Stakes. Of those, 11 went
on to take the Belmont and secure a place in
thoroughbred.MDBO/-.MDNM/racing immortality. Since the young
Cauthen rode Affirmed to victory in his legendary battles with
rival Alydar, six horses have won the first two legs only to falter
in the Belmont. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   The most dramatic near-miss was last year, when Real Quiet lost
the Triple Crown by a nose to Victory Gallop's desperate surge. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   But Charismatic has one advantage the others have lacked: D.
Wayne Lukas. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   The most successful trainer in racing history has won four
Derbys, five Preaknesses and three Belmonts. During one incredible
run from 1994-1996, Lukas-trained horses won seven .MDBO/[
.MDNM/out.MDBO/].MDNM/of eight Triple Crown races, including six in
a row. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Lukas has won classic races with horses of all shapes, colors
and sexes. However, Charismatic, with 33-year-old Antley in the
saddle, will be the first he has brought to the Belmont with a
chance at a sweep. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   ``That's one gap in my resume that I'd love to fill in,'' Lukas
said. &QL; 
nn
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
