<HEADLINE>
&HT;    
 &HT;    MEMORIAL DAY ONLINE
 &HT;    PACKAGES WITH: MEMORIALDAY-COX
 &HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   A sample of remembrances posted on the Virtual Wall:
</P>
<P>
   Veteran: Calvin C. Hudson, of Abbeville, Ga., killed in action
Nov. 11, 1967.
</P>
<P>
   Remembrance by Victor Tunnel, now of Lubbock, Texas.
</P>
<P>
   ``I was in the same platoon as Calvin Clifford Hudson. We were
being overrun, however, through Calvin's last efforts, some of us
were saved that day. I remember him every day of my life and I
would like to meet anyone else that knew him. Love, Vic 'Tex'
Tunnell.''
</P>
<P>
   Veteran: Johnny Ray Bryson, of College Park, killed in action
Jan. 7, 1968.
</P>
<P>
   Remembrance by Dick Miller, who was in Bryson's unit.
</P>
<P>
   ``No one ever saw him without a smile, and whenever there was
need for a boost in morale, he always provided it. I was near him
when he was killed and when I rushed to help him it was clear that
he was gone. He did not suffer and he was not alone Thanks Bryson.
You made better men of all of us. Forever.''
</P>
<P>
   Veteran: John W. Rivers, of Camilla, killed in action July 21,
1967.
</P>
<P>
   Remembrance by Steve Weston.
</P>
<P>
   ``Doc, I remember that day like it was yesterday even though it
has been over 30 years ago. We were pinned down and you and I were
next to each other when the round hit you. I saw the look in your
eyes as if to say help me and then you were dead. I wonder why God
chose you that day and spared me? I have gone on with family and
life but Vietnam still haunts me.''
</P>
<P>
   Veteran: Bobby James, of Bowersville, Ga., killed in action May
13, 1968.
</P>
<P>
   Remembrance by Randy J. Brusse
</P>
<P>
   ``Sgt. Bobby James died in my arms May 13th 1735 hrs. I will
never forget him. I loved him like a brother. Sgt. Randy J.
Brusse.''
</P>
<P>
   More places to mark Memorial Day online:
</P>
<P>
   www.veteransearch.com
</P>
<P>
   www.vfw.org
</P>
<P>
   www.arlingtoncemetery.com
</P>
<P>
   www.mountaindragon.com/memorial
</P>
<P>
   www.no-quarter.org
</P>
<P>
   www.iinc.com/VirtualWall
</P>
