<HEADLINE>
RETURN TO SENDER, ADDRESS THE PROBLEM
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By TOM HOFFARTH  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   My dearest Eli:
</P>
<P>
   Got your letter the other day. Broad-sided me, actually. Pun
intended.
</P>
<P>
   So, you wanna go halves on this L.A. football thing? Great idea.
Why didn't I think of it?
</P>
<P>
   'Cause I did.
</P>
<P>
   But, ya know, even a self-serving, PR-motivated,
court-of-public-opinion-conscious charlatan like myself figured out
that everyone would see right through a flimsy proposal like yours
_ which somehow got released to the media before I even saw it.
</P>
<P>
   Don't flatter yourself anymore.
</P>
<P>
   Listen, we could be partners in crime here. We both know L.A. is
about as apathetic for pro ball as you are pathetic in trying to
unite our evil resources. But I've got my own M.O. (which happen to
be my initials, not incidentally). It doesn't include you.
</P>
<P>
   Look at it this way: I have the match, you have the oily rag,
but only one of us is going to get to light a fire under L.A. fans.
Who's gonna get burned?
</P>
<P>
   I've got my pretty watercolor drawing of the Coliseum. I hear
they could use yours in Houston.
</P>
<P>
   Warmest regards:
</P>
<P>
   M. Ovitz
</P>
<P>
   P.S.: Sorry I accidentally stepped on your Coliseum model in
Atlanta last week. Try crush-proof Play-Doh next time.
</P>
<P>
   _If the Lakers have a secret meeting with Phil Jackson, we'll
!ital!promise not to breathe a word ....
</P>
<P>
   _The Dodgers bring in Jean-Claude Van Osteen to rescue Charlie's
angels. Fair? If the chemistry wasn't creating explosive results,
you gotta change the formula. If anything, the old lefty Osteen
might be able to straighten out what's left of the pitcher known as
Carlos Perez (see: Saturday, in Atlanta, vs. Tom Glavine) ....
</P>
<P>
   _For what it's worth: Frisco Examiner columnist Ray Ratto wasted
newsprint the other day lamenting about how the semi-dreadful
Dodgers are no longer worthy of rooting against by Giants fans.
</P>
<P>
   ``These are not the Dodgers Giant fans paid for when we grew up
watching baseball,'' Ratto rattled on. ``They need the Dodgers as
big and as bad and as snotty as can be, or if that isn't possible,
they need them to be habitual, even record-shattering losers.''
</P>
<P>
   Kinda like the Giants ....
</P>
<P>
   _Hey, it's less than a month before ESPN's X-Games are set to go
in San Fran, but city honchos are trying to raise private cash so
taxpayers don't end up bankrolling the made-for-TV event. Go
bungee-jump off the bridge of your choice and think about how
dreadful that would be ....
</P>
<P>
   _And then you've got the Oakland Tribune and Joe Morgan elbowing
each other to try to buy the Oakland Athletics, and there's George
Zimmer, the guy from the Men's Warehouse, making a bid of his own.
Does this Zimmer have a plate in his head, too?
</P>
<P>
   At least if he succeeds, Zim could dress the boys in something
that matches better with green and yellow socks ....
</P>
<P>
   _We'd pay to have someone arrange a women's tennis doubles team
of Maria Antonia Sanchez-Lorenzo with Anna Kournikova....
</P>
<P>
   _The Raiders announced season tickets are on sale as long as you
purchase the infamous Personal Seat License, which is available
``for as low as $225.'' After that, the tickets cost between $410
and $610....
</P>
<P>
   _There are enough beer logos on NASCAR hoods, so now there's a
new 16-ounce Budweiser can with Dale Earnhardt Jr.'s Chevy on it.
That's to hammer home the idea of drinking and driving, if people
didn't make the connection the first time....
</P>
<P>
   _Former baseball commish Bowie Kuhn has a gig as a commentator
on the Catholic Family Radio network. So explain ``Thou shall not
steal second with a seven-run lead''....
</P>
<P>
   _Attention Todd Marinovich: Master thespian Keanu Reeves needs a
quarterback coach to help him prep for his next movie, ``The
Replacements,'' which is about a buncha guys hired to play in the
NFL....
</P>
<P>
   _Meanwhile, Sir Lawrence Phillips of the Barcelona Dragons has
been hittin' the holes in the NFL Europe League to the tune of a
league-best 700-plus yards rushing and nine TDs through seven
games....
</P>
<P>
   _Clint Eastwood, Arnold Palmer and Peter Ueberroth wanna buy
Pebble Beach for about a billion bucks. The group should include
Mark O'Meara. He's practically owned the course for years.
</P>
