<TEXT>
<P>
   Calling all teachers
</P>
<P>
   Teachers and parents can check out our new Web site,
www.ajc.com/nfk, for learning activities to use with the NFK page
each Monday. You'll find short lessons for every story, as well as
a major project to further explore our story of the week. Plus,
we'll offer ideas to help kids learn about the rest of the paper.
New lesson plans will be posted every Saturday. You can download a
copy or we can e-mail the lesson directly to you.
</P>
<P>
   _ Theresa Walsh Giarrusso
</P>
<P>
   Buckle me up
</P>
<P>
   When you get into your car, do your parents buckle you up? They
should _ it's the law. If you're 5 to 17 years old, you're required
to wear a seat belt even in the back. And your younger brothers and
sisters should be strapped in a car seat until they turn 5. Car
crashes are the leading cause of death for all children. Your
parents can be fined up to $100 if you're not belted in properly.
So, you tell them _ buckle me up! _ Theresa Walsh Giarrusso
</P>
<P>
   Sneezing and wheezing
</P>
<P>
   Aaaaahchooooo! Sounds like you've met the allergy and asthma bad
guys of Darth Mite, Big Bad Roach and Count Igor von Pollen. Now
meet the good guys at www.aaaai.org. You can print out coloring
book pages of the Sneeze and Wheeze Busters _ Dr. Al Lergist, and
his partners, Annie Histamine and Buster Bronchodilasaurus. Plus,
learn ways to help control your allergies and asthma from the
American Academy of Allergy, Asthma and Immunology. _ Theresa Walsh
Giarrusso
</P>
