<TEXT>
<P>
   NEWS FOR KIDS: TOP NEWS FLASHES OF THE WEEK
</P>
<P>
   BALKAN WAR
</P>
<P>
   Yugoslav leader Milosevic charged with crimes
</P>
<P>
   Yugoslavia's leader was charged last week with crimes against
the people of Kosovo. The United Nations war crimes tribunal is
holding President Slobodan Milosevic personally responsible for the
mass killings of ethnic Albanians.
</P>
<P>
   The Yugoslavian government dismissed the charges as another
attack by the United States. Some other world leaders said the
charges would hurt the peace process by angering Milosevic.
</P>
<P>
   Meanwhile, newspapers in England are reporting the United States
and its allies are preparing for a ground war. The paper said
troops will invade Kosovo if the Yugoslavian conflict is not
settled in three weeks.
</P>
<P>
   BORDER DISPUTE
</P>
<P>
   Fighting flares in Kashmir
</P>
<P>
   Fighting between India and Pakistan intensified last week over
land both countries claim. The two nations, located on the Indian
subcontinent, fire daily at each other's troops along the disputed
border of Kashmir. Recently, airstrikes were used by both
countries. Pakistan brought down several aircrafts it claims
crossed into its territory.
</P>
<P>
   India and Pakistan both have nuclear weapons. The United States
and other countries worry that those weapons will be used if the
fighting continues.
</P>
<P>
   India now controls two-thirds of Kashmir. Pakistan holds nearly
one-third, and China has a tiny portion. India and Pakistan each
claim all of the province.
</P>
<P>
   ART
</P>
<P>
   Famous painting restored
</P>
<P>
   In Italy, a cleaned version of the famous ``The Last Supper''
was revealed to the world on Friday. Artists scrubbed and scraped
for 22 years to restore Leonardo da Vinci's 15th century
masterpiece to its original appearance. The 15-foot-tall,
30-foot-long painting, depicting Jesus Christ and his apostles at
the Last Supper, had decayed and turned grimy during the last 500
years. Some artists complain that the restorers went too far and
actually changed the original painting.
</P>
<P>
   _ From news services
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
